    population_ID embedded in unit_id
    <epoch ...>
      <unit id="index.pop_id">
        -36.7667 -36.0667 -35.0000 -33.5333 ... 
      </unit>
    </epoch>
    ...

    No explicit population_ID, units numbered continuously     
    <epoch ...>
      <unit id="index.pop_id">
        -36.7667 -36.0667 -35.0000 -33.5333 ... 
      </unit>
    </epoch>

    No grouping of spikes into units (also compatible with the above 2 pop_id embedding schemes)
    <epoch>
      <spike u=id t="-36.7667" [p="2"]/>
      <spike u=id t="-36.0667" [p="2"]/>
    </epoch>

    The division of data into epochs is optional. 

